{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Inspired by Replicated Softmax (Hinton and Salakhutdinov 2009), DocNADE predicts the probability of a word in a document conditioned on its hidden state which is conditioned on previous words.",
    "Then it interprets topics with a hidden state and infers doctopic distributions with the hidden states of the document.",
    "Gupta et al (2019b) extend Doc-NADE by modeling the bi-directional dependencies between words.",
    "Gupta et al (2019a) then use a LSTM to enable DocNADE to incorporate external knowledge.",
    "Cao et al (2015) also propose an early NTM before VAE-based NTMs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
